node.text:
Best website for coders üßëüèΩ‚Äçüíªüë©üèº‚Äçüíª

If you are a coder or aspiring to be a programmer, you should be aware of these sites and when to use them.

1.¬†@freecodecamp¬†is a perfect resource for you to learn to code for free. Start here. Always.

2. Stack Overflow is the place to go to when you get stuck. 99% chance that the issue you're facing has already been faced before and answers to how to get over the hump.

3. Dev.to is an incredible community of programmers who document their journey as well as post interesting things they have learned along the way. Try to document your journey as well.

4.¬†@geeks_for_geeks¬†is a great way to keep up with programming news as well as for tutorials and interview questions.

5. Scrimba is amazing if you want to interactively learn how to code. Their tutorials allow you to edit and write code alongside the instructors.

6.¬†@github¬†is great to showcase your projects and show employers that you don't just watch coding videos but actually know how to build something. It also gives them an insight into how you write your code.

Make sure to save this and share it with a friend who is on their journey to become a programmer!
